2026-03-29T15:52:01.6944357Z             "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\n- Consolidate CI build logs from multiple orphan branches (one per build) into a single `build-logs` orphan branch with one folder per build\r\n- Use blobless partial clones (`--filter=blob:none`) in both the GitHub Action (writing) and the skill (reading) to avoid downloading unnecessary log content\r\n- Add retry loop with backoff to handle concurrent build push races\r\n- Eliminate the separate branch cleanup step — pruning is now atomic within the push step\r\n\r\n## Changes\r\n\r\n- `.github/workflows/build-and-test.yml` — replaced per-build branch creation + API-based cleanup with single-branch folder-based push using blobless fetch, index manipulation, and retry logic\r\n- `.claude/skills/poll-build-logs/SKILL.md` — switched from branch-name enumeration (`ls-remote` with wildcard) to SHA-based polling + blobless fetch with `-c` config overrides for on-demand blob fetching of specific files\r\n- `CLAUDE.md` — updated skill description\r\n\r\n## Test Plan\r\n\r\n- [ ] Trigger a CI build and verify the `build-logs` branch is created with a single folder\r\n- [ ] Trigger a second build and verify the new folder is added alongside the first\r\n- [ ] Verify old `build-logs/*` per-build branches can be cleaned up after migration\r\n- [ ] Use `/poll-build-logs` skill to verify it correctly detects and reads builds from the new structure\r\n- [ ] After 10+ builds, verify old folders are pruned to keep only 10\r\n",
